---
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';
---

<section
  id="memory"
  class="border-y border-neutral-900 bg-neutral-900/40 px-6 py-20 md:py-28"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
      >
        The knowledge dissolves with the session
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        <p>
          There is a second shift hiding inside the first. Work used to be one
          person per problem; now it is <mark
            >you plus a handful of agents</mark
          >. You operate like an architect: you care that the data flows
          through the system the right way, you do not sit at the keyboard of
          every change. The agent holds those details, the way a coworker used
          to.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every company knows how that story ends. The coworker who knows why
          the payment retry logic looks the way it does changes jobs, and the
          knowledge leaves with them. <strong
            class="font-semibold text-neutral-50"
            >With agents, that does not happen once a year. It happens every
            time a session ends.</strong
          >
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <VizPlaceholder
          label="SessionDissolve island: you + agent on frontend cube, session fades out; then backend cube, fades again"
          ratio="aspect-[16/10]"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <figure
      class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-4xl border-y border-neutral-800 py-10 text-center"
    >
      <p class="text-2xl font-medium leading-snug text-neutral-100 sm:text-3xl">
        Agents are developers who <span class="text-accent"
          >leave after every single task</span
        >.
      </p>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>
